            meaning given by <ref>section 2</ref> of the Registered Fire Engineers Regulation.</def><sourceNote>(<ref href="hk/2025/ln158">L.N. 158 of 2025</ref>)</sourceNote></section><section id="ID_1438403574719_004" name="s2" reason="inEffect" role="regulation" startPeriod="2015-01-29" status="operational" temporalId="s2"><num value="2">2.</num><heading>Authority to issue reports or certificates</heading><leadIn>The Director may make, and with the consent of the Chief Secretary for Administration, given either generally or in any particular case, issue to any person applying therefor in writing and upon payment of the appropriate fee prescribed by these regulations,—  <sourceNote>(<ref href="/hk/1997/ln362">L.N. 362 of 1997</ref>)</sourceNote></leadIn><paragraph id="ID_1438414103520_019" name="a" temporalId="s2_a"><num value="a">(a)</num><content>a report on any fire or other calamity attended by the Fire Services Department;</content></paragraph><paragraph id="ID_1438414103536_006" name="b" temporalId="s2_b"><num value="b">(b)</num><content>a report on any damage caused by fire to any premises, vessel or other property;</content></paragraph><paragraph id="ID_1438414103536_014" name="c" temporalId="s2_c"><num value="c">(c)</num><content>a report or a certificate relating to the structure or condition of any premises, vessel or other property, in relation to fire risks or fire precautions.</content></paragraph><sourceNote>(<ref href="/hk/1987/ln127">L.N. 127 of 1987</ref>)</sourceNote></section><section id="ID_1438403574735_002" name="s3" reason="inEffect" role="regulation" startPeriod="2025-11-01" status="operational" temporalId="s3"><num value="3">3.</num><heading>Fees</heading><text>The fees specified in the third column of the following Table shall be payable to the
